name: Bad News for Badmen... the Mantracker is Back!

description: There's time for reflection as both sides of the conflict regroup: Kamui and other Dragons of Heaven attend school at CLAMP Academy, while Fuma finds his place amoung the Dragons of Earth. But when these two young men, as close as brothers, meet on opposite sides of the battlefield, all hell breaks loose!
name: Interlude

description: An all new classic tale of Thor unchained by the hot creative combo of Mike Carey (X-MEN LEGACY) and Mike Perkins (THE STAND)!! Hela lays siege to Asgard, and demon hordes are loose on Earth. Weakened and alone, Thor must make a dangerous bargain with a mortal woman in order to launch a last assault on the forces of death and chaos - as his enemies were hoping he would. Valiant Vikings, grotesque goblins, and lascivious ladies—what more could any thunder god ask for?
name: Wolves of the North

description: It's the holiday season in Tower City, but the Dynamo 5 kids don't get any time off. They're busy tracking down one of Captain Dynamo's old enemies, who has escaped from prison. But is there more to this simple escape than meets the eye? Featuring a special epilogue section that lays the groundwork for Dynamo 5 in 2011!
name: Holiday Special 2010

description: A holiday. A hold-up. A murder. A car chase. A mound of dog poo. A very large vodka. A fistfight. A kick in the groin. An earthquake. A mutant surfer. A lorry heist. A thousand pairs of panties. A tiny moped. And a gang of killer kangeroos after Tank Girl's scalp. Don't miss this twisted action adventure!
name: Hard Wired For Homicide

description: For two centuries man had explored the Galaxies in his neutron-powered space liners, travelling faster than light for tedious months across the vastness of space until he could reach one of the black holes that littered the Galaxies. These cosmic whirlpools of energy, that sucked light and even stars into themselves, were entered by the spacers, using the incredible cosmic forces there they could by-pass time, and in seconds hurl themselves from one Galaxy to another. But what if an artificial black hole could be created in near space? By using it, months of search and travel could be eliminated. It was to attempt this that the OMEGA EXPERIMENT was set up…
name: The Omega Experiment

description: From issue four, Starblazer published two issues every month.
name: The Edge of Infinity

description:
Out deep in the far reaches of infinity, many strange life forms exist. Some insular, some peaceful, some aggressive, some inquisitive, and some you can't comprehend.

This is the story of three life forms, one human, one aggressive and one from the Purple Planet.
name: The Purple Planet

description: Space wars did not exist. By a series of treaties each Galaxy remained alone and untouched. Earth built a survey ship. Zephyrus, to prospect in deep space. It was this ship that led to the call - "ABANDON EARTH!"
name: Abandon Earth...

description:
An all-star cast of comic creators donate ALL-NEW short tales of comicdom's favorite slasher killers, and all of the proceeds go toward paying off previously stiffed artists! SCOTT ALLIE, J. TORRES, B. CLAY MOORE, GAIL SIMONE, TIM SEELEY and many others unite to tell HACK/SLASH stories-THEIR WAY-in a stand-alone volume that will never be collected in trade! 
 
Story Titles 

  • Butterface
  • Too Cute
  • Campire Stories
  • Equal Opportunity Executioner
  • Malice in Wunderland
  • Blood on the Dancefloor
  • Wallow in Death
  • Rape Van
  • Home, Home On Derange
  • Deadbeats!
  • Hack, Slash Repeat
  • Womb With A View
  • Psyche

description: It's a big day for Mickey Mouse when he gets a brand new car. It's sleek, stylish, top-of-the-line - And it also carries an amazing secret! Strap in with Mickey and Minnie for a joyride that begins innocently enough, but soon grows into a kooky, out-of-control caper across land, sea, and air! Cover by Amy Mebberson.
name: Tools of the Trade

description: It's the exciting conclusion of 'The Menace from the Future!' When Mickey Mouse and Goofy fall into Pete's trap, they have only one chance left to stop a terrifying future from coming true! Too bad it depends on the help of a mysterious stranger. Can she even be trusted? Another epic adventure from modern Mickey master, Casty! Plus: "Pluto at the Beach" by Don Christensen and Jack Bradbury.
name: Mickey Mouse and the Menace From the Future part 2; Pluto At the Beach

description:
Join Catman, Scandal, Deadshot, Ragdoll, and the rest as they hit the road on the run from some of the world's most dangerous killers! A contract has been put out on the lives of the Six, but the sly team has some tricks — and a whole lot of bullets — up their own sleeves in this trade paperback collecting SECRET SIX #1-7!

Back Blurb

THUGS. KILLERS. MANIACS. AND THEY'RE THE GOOD GUYS...

Catman. Deadshot. Scandal Savage. Radgoll. Bane.

Outcosts everywhere but among themselves, they've fought the world's greatest heroes - and the world's deadliest villains - and lived to tell the tale. They're secret Six, and they'll take any job if the price is right... and if they don't end up killing each other first.

But this job is different. Hired to break a supervillain out of jail and bring the priceless artifact she's hiding to Gotham City, these motley mercenaries soon find themselves with a ten million dollar bounty on their heads and an unspeakably vicious crime boss on their heels.

With their precious cargo dividing them as never before, the group embarks on a breakneck road trip from San Francisco to Gotham, leaving a trail of bottles, betrayals and burnt rubber in their wake. Will they make it to Gotham alive? What's the secret of the treasure they're carrying? Who hired them? Who's after them? Who will join their ranks`

And who will stab them in the back?

Superstar writer Gail Simone (WONDER WOMAN) and artist Nicola Scott (BIRDS OF PREY) kick off the Secret Six's thrilling new series with the team's most unpredictable adventure yet!
name: Unhinged

description: The pieces fall into place and Emperor Kurr's master plan is revealed at last! The world is on the brink of annihilation and Savage Dragon has his finger on the button! The events in this issue are so unexpected-so shocking-that we can't show you the cover to this issue without spoiling the surprise! It's unlike anything you've ever read or imagined! This is all building to the most explosive finale in the history of comics! Prepare to have your senses shattered and your mind blown! This is the big one! The countdown to the end of the world ends here! Comes with our highest possible recommendation!
name: Emperor Dragon, Part Five: The Way It Ends

description:
A doomsday device capable of destroying whole planets has been created, but an accident during the first demonstration firing puts the universe in danger.

Lieutenant Tom Carlton is sent across space to intercept the beam of the weapon and avert disaster.
name: The Planet Cracker

description: Throughout the Galaxy scientific probes searched the million worlds scattered in remote space. Some discovered worlds of indescribable beauty and wealth, others found inert and barren planets long ago destroyed by some unrecorded disaster … and one probe encountered The Overlords of Oltair.
name: The Overlords of Oltair
Mark Sabor... Gladiator of the Future!
